scripts.comment: BJC CS10 Project 1: Wordle™-lite Your job is to fill in the three blocks below; when they are all correct, the game should play exactly as described in the specification.

custom-block.s: matching "green" slots between guess: %txt and secret: %txt
custom-block.comment: Reports a word of letters or dashes to indicate the matching slots between guess and secret, the same length as secret, in which every matched letter is the letter itself, and any missed letter is a dash.

custom-block.s: update score based on matched slots: %txt and score: %n
custom-block.comment: Reports an updated score based on the old score minus 10 (cost for a guess) plus the number of slots that matched (were not “-”).

custom-block.s: Play Worldle™-lite
custom-block.comment: Testing. Here are some examples, but you should add your own...

custom-block.s: game over? guess: %txt secret: %txt score: %n
custom-block.comment: Should return false. The guess doesn't match, but the score still positive.

custom-block.s: game over? guess: %txt secret: %txt score: %n
game over? guess: %txt secret: %txt score: %n
custom-block.comment: Should return true. Score not positive.

custom-block.s: game over? guess: %txt secret: %txt score: %n
custom-block.comment: Should return true. Score not positive.

custom-block.s: game over? guess: %txt secret: %txt score: %n
custom-block.comment: Should return true. Guess matches and the score not positive.
